data.title: Greatest team nickname ever
data.meta_description:
For some reason, Mississippi is fairly lean on truly bizarre team nicknames, but we have a few that are unusual:

Taylorsville Tartars
East Union...
data.text:
Port Gibson is going through an identity crisis, too. Used to be the Blue Waves. In the last couple of years they've started calling themselves the Port Gibson Blue Wave Fighting Sharks.

It sounds like a move from a badly-dubbed episode of "Dragonball Z".

Nothing that comes out of Port Gibson will ever surprise me, or shock me.

I'm amazed that I haven't contributed to this in some way.

From the Hoosier state:

Active

Clay City & Eminence Eels

Crawfordsville Athenians (the home of Lew Wallace, C-Ville is the "Athens of the Midwest" or something like that)

Delphi Oracles

Fort Wayne South Archers

Forest Park Rangers

Frankfort Hot Dogs

Indianapolis Northwest Space Pioneers (the school opened in the 1960s)

LaPorte Slicers

Madison-Grant Argylls

Mishawaka Cavemen (Marengo -- where there are actually caves -- also used the name)

Pendleton Heights Arabians (named after the horses, not the race of people )

Rising Sun Shiners

Shoals Jug Rox

Tell City Marksmen

Vincennes Alices (named after the book "Alice of Old Vincennes")

Washington Hatchets

Consolidated out of existence

Advance Osceolons, which joined the Thorntown Kewasakees to form the ... Western Boone Stars (yes, lame nicknames are the heart of consolidated schools).

Arlington Purple Breezes

Banquo Ghosts

Battle Ground Tomahawks

Bedford Stonecutters (in the heart of limestone country)

Bloomingdale Academy Immortals

Burlington Polar Cubs

Cambridge City Wampus Cats

Chili Polar Bears

Concannon Cannons

Cory Apple Boys

Cynthiana Annas

DePauw Blue River Echoes

Edwardsport Powers

Farmersburg Plowboys

Fort Branch Twigs

Hartford City Airedales (and its cousin, the Mt. Ayr Ayrdales)

Holton Warhorses

Huntingburg Happy Hunters (who consolidated with the Holland Dutchmen to form ... the Southridge Raiders ... ugh!)

Hymera Shakamaks (named after a nearby forest ... there has since been a consolidated school named Shakamak ... of which Hymera is not a part).

Ireland Spuds

Jackson Twp. Stonewalls (and we're nowhere near the Confederacy ... Roanoke also used the name)

Klondike Nuggets

Ladoga Canners

Lincoln Railsplitters (who later consolidated with the Onward Redcoats)

Lynnville Lyndies

Montezuma Aztecs, Mecca Arabs & Rosedale Hot Shots consolidated together (to form another school with a lame name, the Riverton Parke Panthers)

Michigantown Ganders

Milton Sharpshooters

Monroe City Blue Jeans (named after former Gov. Blue Jeans Williams, a native of the town)

Owensville Kickapoos

Pine Village Pine Knots

Plainville, Wanatah & Perry Central Midgets

Poseyville Posies

Raleigh Sir Walters

Remington Rifles

Roll Red Rollers

Scircleville Ringers

Smithville Skibos

Spencer Cops (because Spencer was once the "C"enter "O"f "P"opulation in the U.S.)

Stinesville Quarry Lads

Summitville Goblins

Swayzee & Urbana Speed Kings

Terre Haute Gerstmeyer Black Cats

Upland Yeomen

Wallace Peppers

Waynetown Gladiators

West Baden Sprudels

Wheatfield Shockers

Whitewater Twp. Elkhorns

Williamsport Bingy Bombers

I'd say I miss them too, ... but my wife might find out.

Loved the bumpersticker and wish I had one. Ah, the sweet and innocent times of the mid-1980s.

I know of a Senior A hockey team here in Ontario called the Muskies. The story I was told was, they were to have been called the Huskies. But when their New York Ranger-style sweaters arrived, for some reason there was an "M" in place of the "H."

And they remain the Muskies today, with a fish logo and everything - they're even nicknamed the Fish - even though the town in which they play doesn't have a river, a harbour or any kind of body of water anywhere nearby.

Out here in the AJHL -- alberta junior hockey league -- we have the Olds Grizzlys. Apparently they can't spell in Olds. Innocent enough, sure, but after having to write it out for a hockey season you feel rather stupid doing so. I have now had to write it out for six of my eight years in the business.
